>>
>>Your biggest problem is probably your cache size.  I'm not sure what the limit 
>>is, but I would be pretty sure that a 64K secondary cache can only handle 8 or 
>>16 MB of RAM.  OS2 loads itself into memory from the top down.  So if you 
>>can't cache all of your RAM then OS2 will be running at least partly in 
>>uncached RAM.
>>

>Is this cache thing really true ? I question becasue I had no idea of 
>this. If this is, any idea what the limit is for 256 Kb cache ?

On my system with a RAM limit of 32MB, the cache limit is 256 KB, thus
the motherboard manufacturer assumed 32 MB was the limit.

BTW, I had a similar experience when I upgraded from 8 MB to 20 MB on a
64 KB cache system.  Ran like a snail until I replaced the cache with
256 KB.  Cache is cheap compared to RAM.

